TIL: Punderstanding

Computational Pun-derstanding that is.

Vincent Warmerdam koaning.io
2022-10-05

It turns out, not a joke, that there is a research group working on Computer-Assisted Translation of Humorous Wordplay. They can be found over at punderstanding.of.ai and its, again, not a joke.

Just from browsing around here I learned a ton about this field.

  • Heres one on a model called PunCAT that tries to translate puns in language. The tool can be found on Github.
  • Theres an attempt to predict humour by using Gaussian Processes. The dataset for this task is called SemEval-2017 and it contains sentences like Money is the Root of All Evil. For more info, send $10.. The question is, can humor be detected?
  • Theres a contest called JokeR thats all about Automatic Pun and Humour Translation.
  • Through this group, I also learned that there is an International Journal of Humor Research

Today I learned.

It does seem like a very hard domain to expect results from, just because natural language is so flexible but also because humor depends so much on culture/background that Im having trouble thinking of a ground truth.
